%html
  %head
    %title= "Tweetfindr :: How to search for #tags or @users"
    %link{:rel => 'stylesheet', :href => 'vend.css', :type => 'text/css'}
  %body
    %center
      %img{:src => 'hat.gif', :title => 'Powered by Sinatra and Twitter', :class => 'mainpic'}
      %h1= "twitter search for #tags or @users"
      %hr{:width => '80%'}
      %br
      To search for 
      %span{ :class => 'yellow'} #sinatra
      , just put "sinatra" at the end of this url like so: 
      %a{:href => '/sinatra'} http://tweetfindr.com/sinatra
      %br
      %br
      To search for a user like 
      %span{:class => 'yellow'} @algore
      , put "@algore" at the end: 
      %a{:href => '/@algore'} http://tweetfindr.com/@algore
      %br

      %hr{:width => '80%'}
      %div{:class => 'copyright'}
        %small= 'Powered by <a href=/sinatra>Sinatra</a> + <a href=/twitter>Twitter</a> (<a href="http://github.com/mdw/twitvend/tree/master">the source</a>)'

